  ################
  # 5) Defection #
  ################
  # 
  # Method: Defection means a cogen unit (non-utility) stops selling electricity
  # to the grid to comply with the CER. It is modelled by setting UnPSoMaxGridFraction to 0.
  # In NextGrid, the defection is only made on the 'grid part' of the plant which results
  # in reducing the the total installed capacity of the plant (only the 'indus part' keeps generating)
  # This reduction is not modelled in E2020 because it is judged unrealistic in real world

  for unit in Units

    if UnCode[unit] == "AB00035100101"
      years = collect(Yr(2050):Yr(2050))
      for year in years
        xUnGCCR[unit,year] = -16.1
        UnPSoMaxGridFraction[unit,year] = 0
      end
    end

    if UnCode[unit] == "AB_Air_Liquide"
